II.\tab Signal to Noise Ratio\par 
\tab \tab most events are of short duration, so high speed devices are required to provide suit\-able time resolution, and large aperture is needed to provide adequate signal to noise ratio during each integration\par 
\tab \tab \tab high speed CCD is best\par 
\tab \tab \tab slow readout CCD might work if image drifted across chip (orthogonal to Saturn-satellite axis), though saturation may be a problem\par 
\tab \tab \tab high speed aperture photometer may work, though see below\par 
